new_version_errors.1.0.0:
The recipe did not change in the version migration, a URL did not hash, or there is jinja2 syntax the bot cannot handle!

Please check the URLs in your recipe with version '1.0.0' to make sure they exist!

We also found the following errors:

 - recipe did not appear to change even though the bot said it should have

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.0.0" %}

package:
  name: "cyanure"
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/thomasryck/cyanure/archive/{{ version }}/cyanure-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: a35f4c17e909b1740fe520fcb6707de8e95032367f734565eb99d0056b4c958e
    
build:
  number: 3
  script:
    - "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}
    - llvm-openmp  # [osx]
    - python
    - libgomp  # [linux]
    - intel-openmp  # [win]
  host:
    - python
    - libblas
    - liblapack
    - numpy >=1.21.6
    - pip
  run:
    - python
    - scipy
    - scikit-learn
    - {{ pin_compatible('numpy') }}
    

test:
  imports:
    - cyanure
  source_files:
   - test/*.py
  requires:
    - pytest
    - pandas
  commands:
    - pytest

about:
  home: https://inria-thoth.github.io/cyanure/welcome.html
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'A Toolbox for Empirical Risk Minimization'
  description: | 
   Cyanure is an open-source C++ software package with a Python 3 interface. 
   The goal of Cyanure is to provide state-of-the-art solvers 
   for learning linear models, based on stochastic variance-reduced stochastic optimization 
   with acceleration mechanisms and Quasi-Newton principles.
  dev_url: https://github.com/inria-thoth/cyanure
  doc_url: https://inria-thoth.github.io/cyanure/welcome.html

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - thomasryck
    - jmairal
